raw_data.title: Employee and Management Development Programs
raw_data.description: Employee and Management Development Programs delivered virtually or onsite covering a range of subjects from work-life balance, stress management and personal development, to communication, resilience, management change and other personal and workplace topics.
raw_data.required_certifications_or_licenses: State Licensed   Masters Level Mental Health professional such as a Licensed Clinical Social Worker or equivalent.

raw_data.title: Onsite Counseling
raw_data.description: EAP Counseling services are available at the Agency’s worksite on a per hour basis. At a minimum, our counselors meet the following criteria:  • Doctorate or Masters Degree in a Mental Health field from an accredited college or university • Licensed by the State to provide mental health services  • Three years or more of postgraduate experience providing assessments, short-term solution focused counseling and referring clients with a broad range of behavioral problems, including substance abuse
raw_data.required_certifications_or_licenses: State Licensed   Masters Level Mental Health professional such as a Licensed Clinical Social Worker or equivalent.
